obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (25915)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00001_196341_1517807318207&sectionId=25915&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00001_196341_1517807318207
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Textiles Committee`
  line `Act, 1963.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India ^1***.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^2`
  line `, as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "except the State of Jammu Kashmir" omitted by Act 51 of 1973, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-1-1975).`
  line
  line `2 . 22nd August, 1964, vide notification No. S.O. 2913(E), dated the 22nd August, 1964, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary,`
  line `Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (25916)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00001_196341_1517807318207&sectionId=25916&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00001_196341_1517807318207
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless there is anything repugnant in the subject or context,--`
  line
  line `(a) "Chairman" means the Chairman of the Committee.`
  line
  line `(b) "Committee" means the Committee established under section 3;`
  line
  line `^1[(ba) "fiber" means man-made fiber including regenerated cellulose rayon, nylon and the like.]`
  line
  line `(c) "Fund" means the Textile Fund referred to in section 7;`
  line
  line `^1[(ca) "handloom industries" has the meaning assigned to it in the Khadi and Other Handloom`
  line `Industries Development (Additional Excise, Duty on Cloth) Act, 1953 (12 of 1953);]`
  line
  line `(d) "member" means a member of the Committee and includes the Chairman and the`
  line Vice-Chairman;
  line
  line `^1[(da) "powerloom" means a loom which is worked by power as defined in clause (g) of section 2`
  line `of the Factories Act, 1948 (63 of 1948), and which is used or capable of being used only for weaving`
  line `cloth wholly or partly out of cotton yarn or woollen yarn, or fiber, or any kind of mixed yarn;`
  line
  line `(db) "powerloom industry" means an industry in which a manufacturer of textiles has, at any time`
  line `during the period fixed by the Committee under clause (a) of sub-section (5) of section 5A, not more`
  line `than fifty powerlooms (without any spinning plants) in the factory or factories owned, controlled or`
  line `managed by him.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this clause, the expression "factory" has the meaning assigned`
  line `to it in the Factories Act, 1948 (63 of 1948):]`
  line
  line `(e) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(f) "textile machinery" means the equipment employed directly or indirectly for the processing of`
  line `textile fiber into yarn and for the manufacture of fabric therefrom by weaving or knitting and includes`
  line `equipment used either wholly or partly for the finishing, folding, or packing of textiles;`
  line
  line `^2[(g) "textiles" means any fabric or cloth or yarn or garment or any other article made wholly or`
  line `in part of--`
  line
  line `(i) cotton; or`
  line
  line `(ii) wool; or`
  line
  line `(iii) silk; or`
  line
  line `(iv) artificial silk or other fiber,`
  line
  line `and includes fiber;]`
  line
  line `(h) "Vice-Chairman" means the Vice-Chairman of the Committee.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 51 of 1973, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-1-1975).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for clause (g) (w.e.f. 1-1-1975).`
obj_root_law_sections_2_a:
  sectionId (25917)
  sectionNo 2A
  orderNo 3
  title `Construction of references to any law not in force, or any functionary not in existence, in the State of Jammu and Kashmir.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 51 of 1973, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-1-1975).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00001_196341_1517807318207&sectionId=25917&sectionno=2A&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00001_196341_1517807318207
obj_root_law_sections_2_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[2A. Construction of references to any law not in force, or any functionary not in existence, in the`
  line `State of Jammu and Kashmir].--Omitted by the Jammu and Kashmir Reorganization (Adaptation of`
  line `Central Laws) Order, 2020, vide notification No. S.O. 1123(E) dated (18-3-2020) and Vide Union`
  line `Territory of Ladakh Reorganisation (Adaptation of Central Laws) Order, 2020, notification No.`
  line `S.O.3774(E), dated (23-10-2020). Earlier ins. by Act 51 of 1973, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-1-1975).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (25918)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 4
  title `Establishment of Textiles Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00001_196341_1517807318207&sectionId=25918&sectionno=3&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00001_196341_1517807318207
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, establish with effect from such date as may be specified in the notification, a Committee`
  line `to be known as the Textiles Committee, which shall be a body corporate having perpetual succession and`
  line `a common seal with power to acquire, hold and dispose of property and to contract and may, by that`
  line `name, sue or be sued.`
  line
  line `(2) The Head Office of the Committee shall be in Bombay.`
  line
  line `(3) The Committee shall consist of--`
  line
  line `(a) a Chairman to be appointed by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(b) a Vice-Chairman who shall be the Textile Commissioner, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(c) a Joint Secretary to the Government of India to be appointed by the Central Government,`
  line `ex officio;`
  line
  line `(d) such other members as the Central Government may think fit to appoint who, in the opinion of`
  line `that Government, have special knowledge or practical experience in matters relating to the textile`
  line `industry and trade and the manufacture of textile machinery.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (25919)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 5
  title `Functions of the Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00001_196341_1517807318207&sectionId=25919&sectionno=4&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00001_196341_1517807318207
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act, the functions of the`
  line `Committee shall generally be to ensure by such measures, as it thinks fit, standard qualities of textiles`
  line `both for internal marketing and export purposes and the manufacture and use of standard type of textile`
  line machinery.
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the provisions of sub-section (1), the Committee may--`
  line
  line `(a) undertake, assist and encourage, scientific, technological and economic research in-textile`
  line `industry and textile machinery,`
  line
  line `(b) promote export of textiles and textile machinery and carry on propaganda for that purpose;`
  line
  line `^1[(c) establish or adopt or recognise standard specifications for--`
  line
  line `(i) textiles, and`
  line
  line `(ii) packing materials used in the packing of textiles or textile machinery,`
  line
  line `for the purposes of export and for internal consumption and affix suitable marks on such standardised`
  line `varieties of textiles and packing materials;]`
  line
  line `(d) specify the type of quality control or inspection which will be applied to textiles or`
  line `textile machinery;`
  line
  line `^2[(da) provide for training in the techniques of quality control to be applied to textiles or`
  line `textile machinery;]`
  line
  line `(e) provide for the inspection and examination of--`
  line
  line `(i) textiles;`
  line
  line `(ii) textile machinery at any stage of manufacture and also while it is in use at mill-heads;`
  line
  line `^2[(iii) packing materials used in the packing of textiles or textile machinery;]`
  line
  line `(f) establish laboratories and test houses for the testing of textiles;`
  line
  line `(g) provide for testing textiles and textile machinery in laboratories and test houses other than`
  line `those established under clause (f);`
  line
  line `(h) collect statistics for any of the above mentioned purposes from--`
  line
  line `(i) manufacturers of, and dealers in, textiles;`
  line
  line `(ii) manufacturers of textile machinery; and`
  line
  line `(iii) such other persons as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(i) advice on all matters relating to the development of textile industry and the production of`
  line `textile machinery;`
  line
  line `(j) provide for such other matters as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) In the discharge of its functions, the Committee shall be bound by such directions as the Central`
  line `Government may, for reasons to be stated in writing, give to it from time to time.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 5, ibid., for clause (c) (w.e.f. 1-1-1975).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 5, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-1-1975).`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (25920)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 6
  title `Powers of the Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00001_196341_1517807318207&sectionId=25920&sectionno=5&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00001_196341_1517807318207
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `The Committee may exercise all such powers as may be necessary or`
  line `expedient for the purpose of carrying out its functions under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5_a:
  sectionId (25921)
  sectionNo 5A
  orderNo 7
  title `Imposition of cess on textiles and textile machinery manufactured in India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 51 of 1973, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-1-1975).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00001_196341_1517807318207&sectionId=25921&sectionno=5A&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00001_196341_1517807318207
obj_root_law_sections_5_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[5A. Imposition of cess on textiles and textile machinery manufactured in India.--(1) There`
  line `shall be levied and collected as a cess for the purposes of this Act a duty of excise on all textiles and on`
  line `all textile machinery manufactured in India at such rate, not exceeding one per cent. ad valorem as the`
  line `Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, fix:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such cess shall be levied on textiles manufactured from out of handloom or`
  line `powerloom industry.`
  line
  line `(2) The duty of excise levied under sub-section (1) shall be in addition to any cess or duty leviable on`
  line `textiles or textile machinery under any other law for the time being in force.`
  line
  line `(3) The duty of excise levied under sub-section (1) shall be collected by the Committee, in accordance`
  line `with the rules made in this behalf, from every manufacturer of textiles or textile machinery`
  line `(hereinafter in this section and in sections 5C and 5D referred to as the manufacturer).`
  line
  line `(4) The manufacturer shall pay to the Committee the amount of the duty of excise levied under`
  line `sub-section (1) within one month from the date on which he receives a notice of demand therefore from`
  line `the Committee.`
  line
  line `(5) For the purpose of enabling the Committee to assess the amount of the duty of excise levied under`
  line `sub-section (1),--`
  line
  line `(a) the Committee shall, by notification in the Gazette of India, fix the period in respect of which`
  line `assessments shall be made; and`
  line
  line `(b) every manufacturer shall furnish to the Committee a return, not later than fifteen days after the`
  line `expiry of the period to which the return relates, specifying the total quantity of textiles or textile`
  line `machinery manufactured by him during the said period and such other particulars as may`
  line `be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(6) If any manufacturer fails to furnish the return referred to in sub-section (5) within the time`
  line `specified therein, or furnishes a return which the Committee has reason to believe is incorrect or`
  line `defective, the Committee may assess the amount of the duty of excise in such manner as may`
  line `be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(7) Any manufacturer aggrieved by an assessment made under this section may appeal to the`
  line `Tribunal, constituted under section 5B for cancellation or modification of the assessment.]`
obj_root_law_sections_5_b:
  sectionId (25922)
  sectionNo 5B
  orderNo 8
  title `Constitution of Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 51 of 1973, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-1-1975).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00001_196341_1517807318207&sectionId=25922&sectionno=5B&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00001_196341_1517807318207
obj_root_law_sections_5_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[5B. Constitution of Tribunal.--The Central Government may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, constitute a Tribunal consisting of one person, who is or has been, or is qualified for appointment`
  line `as a Judge of a High Court and who is not connected with the Committee to exercise the powers and`
  line `discharge the functions conferred or imposed on the Tribunal by or under this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_5_c:
  sectionId (25923)
  sectionNo 5C
  orderNo 9
  title `Hearing of appeals by Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_c_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 51 of 1973, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-1-1975).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00001_196341_1517807318207&sectionId=25923&sectionno=5C&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00001_196341_1517807318207
obj_root_law_sections_5_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[5C. Hearing of appeals by Tribunal.--(1) An appeal under sub-section (7) of section 5A may be`
  line `preferred to the Tribunal within one month from the date on which the notice of demand regarding the`
  line `assessment is served on the manufacturer:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Tribunal may admit an appeal after the expiration of the period aforesaid, if it is`
  line `satisfied that the appellant had sufficient cause for not preferring it within that period.`
  line
  line `(2) Every appeal referred to in sub-section (1) shall be in the prescribed form and shall be verified in`
  line `the prescribed manner and shall be accompanied with such fees as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The Tribunal shall fix a day and place for the hearing of the appeal and shall give notice of the`
  line `same to the appellant and to the Committee.`
  line
  line `(4) The Tribunal may, after giving the appellant and the Committee an opportunity of being heard,`
  line `pass such order thereon as it thinks fit:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order enhancing the assessment shall he made unless the appellant has had a`
  line `reasonable opportunity of showing cause against such enhancement.`
  line
  line `(5) The Tribunal shall send a copy of any order passed under this section to the appellant and to the`
  line `Committee and such order shall be final.`
  line
  line `(6) In discharging the functions under this section, the Tribunal may, subject to any rules that may be`
  line `made in this behalf, follow such procedure as it thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(7) The Tribunal shall have all the powers of a civil court while trying a suit under the Code of Civil`
  line `Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), in respect of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) summoning and enforcing the attendance of any person and examining him on oath;`
  line
  line `(b) requiring the discovery and production of any documents;`
  line
  line `(c) receiving evidence on affidavits;`
  line
  line `(d) requisitioning any public record or copy thereof from any court or office;`
  line
  line `(e) issuing commissions for the examination of witnesses and documents;`
  line
  line `(f) any other matter which may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(8) The expenses of the Tribunal shall be borne by the Central Government.]`
obj_root_law_sections_5_d:
  sectionId (25924)
  sectionNo 5D
  orderNo 10
  title `Recovery of duty of excise.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_d_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 51 of 1973, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-1-1975).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00001_196341_1517807318207&sectionId=25924&sectionno=5D&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00001_196341_1517807318207
obj_root_law_sections_5_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[5D. Recovery of duty of excise.--If any manufacturer fails to pay the duty of excise levied under`
  line `section 5A, within the period specified in sub-section (4) of that section, or where an appeal has been`
  line `preferred by him against an order of assessment under sub-section (7) of section 5A, within one month`
  line `from the date of disposal of such appeal, the duty payable by him shall be recoverable as an arrear of land`
  line revenue.]
obj_root_law_sections_5_e:
  sectionId (25925)
  sectionNo 5E
  orderNo 11
  title `Power to exempt.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_e_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 51 of 1973, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-1-1975).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00001_196341_1517807318207&sectionId=25925&sectionno=5E&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00001_196341_1517807318207
obj_root_law_sections_5_e_content:
  string
  line `^1[5E. Power to exempt.--If the Central Government is of opinion that in the interests of trade or in the`
  line `public interest it is necessary so to do, it may, by notification in the Official Gazette, exempt such variety`
  line `of textiles or such textiles machinery as may be specified in the notification from the whole or any part of`
  line `the duty of excise leviable under section 5A.]`
obj_root_law_sections_5_f:
  sectionId (25926)
  sectionNo 5F
  orderNo 12
  title `Payment of proceeds of cess to the Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_f_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 51 of 1973, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-1-1975).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00001_196341_1517807318207&sectionId=25926&sectionno=5F&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00001_196341_1517807318207
obj_root_law_sections_5_f_content:
  string
  line `^1[5F. Payment of proceeds of cess to the Committee.--The proceeds of the duty of excise collected`
  line `under section 5A, reduced by the cost of collection as determined by the Central Government, shall first`
  line `be credited to the Consolidated Fund of India and the Central Government may, after due appropriate`
  line `made by Parliament by law, pay to the Committee from out of such proceeds, such sums of money as it`
  line `thinks fit for being utilised for the purposes of this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (25927)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 13
  title `Grants by Central Government to the Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00001_196341_1517807318207&sectionId=25927&sectionno=6&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00001_196341_1517807318207
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `For the purpose of enabling the Committee`
  line `to discharge its functions under this Act, the Central Government may, after due appropriation made by`
  line `Parliament by law in this behalf, pay to the Committee in each financial year such sums of money as that`
  line `Government considers necessary by way of grant, loan or otherwise.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (25928)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 14
  title `Constitution of Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes `1 . Ins. by Act 51 of 1973, s. 7 (w.e.f. 1-1-1975),`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00001_196341_1517807318207&sectionId=25928&sectionno=7&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00001_196341_1517807318207
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Committee shall have a Fund to be called the Textiles Fund and`
  line `there shall be credited thereto--`
  line
  line `(a) all moneys transferred to it under clause (a) of sub-section (2) of section 24;`
  line
  line `^1[(aa) the proceeds of the duty of excise made over, to the committee by the Central Government`
  line `under section 5F;]`
  line
  line `(b) all moneys paid by the Central Government under section 6;`
  line
  line `(c) all fees and other charges levied under this Act;`
  line
  line `(d) all moneys received by the Committee by way of grant, gift, donation, contribution, transfer`
  line `or otherwise.`
  line
  line `(2) The moneys in the Fund shall be applied for--`
  line
  line `(a) meeting the pay and allowances of the officers and other employees of the Committee and`
  line `other administrative expenses of the Committee;`
  line
  line `(b) carrying out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) All moneys in the Fund shall be deposited in the State Bank of India or be invested in such`
  line `securities, as may be approved by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (25929)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 15
  title `Standing or ad hoc Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 8, ibid., for sub-sections (2) and (3) (w.e.f. 1-1-1975).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00001_196341_1517807318207&sectionId=25929&sectionno=8&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00001_196341_1517807318207
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Committee may constitute Standing Committees or`
  line `ad hoc Committees for exercising any power or discharging any duty of the Committee or for inquiring`
  line `into or reporting and advising on any matter which the Committee may refer to them.`
  line
  line `^1[(2) A Standing Committee or an ad hoc Committee constituted under sub-section (1) may include`
  line `persons who are not members of the Committee, but their number shall not exceed one`
  line `half of its strength.]`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (25930)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 16
  title `Officers and other employees of the Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00001_196341_1517807318207&sectionId=25930&sectionno=9&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00001_196341_1517807318207
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall, in`
  line `consultation with the Committee, appoint a person to be the Secretary of the Committee.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to such rules as may be made by the Central Government in this behalf, the Committee`
  line `may appoint such other officers and employees as it considers necessary for the efficient performance of`
  line `its functions.`
  line
  line `(3) The methods of appointment, the conditions of service and the scales of pay of the officers and`
  line `other employees of the Committee shall,--`
  line
  line `(a) as respects the Secretary, be such as may be prescribed; and`
  line
  line `(b) as respect the other officers and employees, be such as may be determined by regulations`
  line `made by the Committee under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (25931)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 17
  title `Transfer of service of existing employees to the Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00001_196341_1517807318207&sectionId=25931&sectionno=10&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00001_196341_1517807318207
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this`
  line `Act, every person employed by the Cotton Textiles Fund Committee constituted under section 5 of the`
  line `Cotton Textiles Fund Ordinance, 1944 (34 of 1944), immediately before the date of establishment of the`
  line `Committee shall on and from such date, become an employee of the Committee with such designation as`
  line `the Committee may determine and shall hold his office or service therein by the same tenure, at the same`
  line `remuneration and upon the same terms and conditions as he would have held on such date if the`
  line `Committee had not been established and shall continue to do so unless and until his employment in the`
  line `committee is terminated or until such tenure, remuneration and terms and conditions are duly altered by`
  line `the Committee:`
  line
  line `Provided that the tenure, remuneration and terms and conditions of service of any such person shall`
  line `not be altered to his disadvantage without the previous approval of the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (25932)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 18
  title Inspection.
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00001_196341_1517807318207&sectionId=25932&sectionno=11&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00001_196341_1517807318207
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Committee may, on application made to it or otherwise, direct an officer`
  line `specially authorised in that behalf to examine the quality of textiles or the suitability of textile machinery`
  line `for use at the time of manufacture or while in use in a textile mill and submit a report to the Committee,`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to any rules made under this Act, such an officer shall have power to--`
  line
  line `(a) inspect any operation carried on in connection with the manufacture of textiles or textile`
  line `machinery in relation to which construction particulars, marks or inspection standards have`
  line `been specified;`
  line
  line `(b) take samples of any article or of any material or substance used in any article or process in`
  line `relation to which construction particulars, marks or inspection standards have been specified;`
  line
  line `(c) exercise such other powers as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) On receipt of the report referred to in sub-section (1), the Committee may tender such advice, as it`
  line `may deem fit, to the manufacturer of textiles, the manufacturer of textile machinery and the applicant.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (25933)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 19
  title `Levy of fees for inspection and examination.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00001_196341_1517807318207&sectionId=25933&sectionno=12&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00001_196341_1517807318207
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Committee may levy such fees as may`
  line `be prescribed--`
  line
  line `(a) for inspection and examination of textiles;`
  line
  line `^1* * * * *`
  line
  line `^2[(b)] for any ^3[special] service which the Committee may render to the manufacturers`
  line `^4[or exporters] of textiles and textile machinery:`
  line
  line `^4[Provided that no fees shall be levied in respect of inspection and examination of textiles on which a`
  line `duty of excise is leviable under this Act:]`
  line
  line `^5[Provided further that] the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `exempt from the payment of fees, generally or in any particular case.`
  line
  line `(2) Any sum payable to the Committee under sub-section (1) may be recovered as an arrear of land`
  line revenue.
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Clause (b) omitted by Act 51 of 1973, s. 9 (w.e.f. 1-1-1975).`
  line
  line `2. Clause (c) re-lettered as clause (b) thereof by s. 9, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-1-1975).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 9, ibid., for "other" (w.e.f. 1-1-1975).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by s. 9, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-1-1975).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 9, ibid., for "Provided that" (w.e.f. 1-1-1975).`
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (25934)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 20
  title `Accounts and audit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00001_196341_1517807318207&sectionId=25934&sectionno=13&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00001_196341_1517807318207
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Committee shall maintain proper accounts and other relevant`
  line `records and prepare an annual statement of accounts, including the balance-sheet, in accordance with such`
  line `general directions as may be issued, and in such form as may be prescribed, by the Central Government in`
  line `consultation with the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(2) The accounts of the Committee shall be audited annually by the Comptroller and Auditor-General`
  line `of India and any expenditure incurred by him in connection with such audit shall be payable by the`
  line `Committee to the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(3) The Comptroller and Auditor-General of India and any person appointed by him in connection`
  line `with the audit of the accounts of the Committee shall have the same rights and privileges and authority in`
  line `connection with such audit as the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India has in connection with the`
  line `audit of Government accounts, and, in particular, shall have the right to demand the production of books`
  line `accounts, connected vouchers and other documents and papers and to inspect any of the offices of the`
  line Committee.
  line
  line `(4) The accounts of the Committee as certified by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India or`
  line `any other person appointed by him in this behalf, together with the audit report thereon, shall be`
  line `forwarded annually to the Central Government and that Government shall cause the same to be laid`
  line `before each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (25935)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 21
  title `Delegation of powers and duties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00001_196341_1517807318207&sectionId=25935&sectionno=14&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00001_196341_1517807318207
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `The Committee may, by general or special order in writing,`
  line `direct that all or any of the powers or duties which may be exercised or discharged by it shall, in such`
  line `circumstances and under such conditions, if any, as may be specified in its order, be exercised or`
  line `discharged also by any officer or employee of the Committee specified in this behalf in the order.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (25936)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 22
  title `Acts or proceedings of Committee not to be invalidated.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00001_196341_1517807318207&sectionId=25936&sectionno=15&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00001_196341_1517807318207
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `No act or proceeding of the`
  line `Committee shall be invalidated merely by reason of--`
  line
  line `(a) any vacancy, in, or any defect in the constitution of, the Committee; or`
  line
  line `(b) any defect in the appointment of a person acting as a member of the Committee; or`
  line
  line `(c) any irregularity in the procedure of the Committee not affecting the merits of the case.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (25937)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 23
  title `Officers and employees of the Committee to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00001_196341_1517807318207&sectionId=25937&sectionno=16&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00001_196341_1517807318207
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `All officers and employees`
  line `of the Committee shall, while acting or purporting to act in pursuance of the provisions of this Act or of`
  line `any rule or regulation made thereunder, be deemed to be public servants within the meaning of section 21`
  line `of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (25938)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 24
  title `Power to prohibit exports and internal marketing of textiles and textile machinery.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00001_196341_1517807318207&sectionId=25938&sectionno=17&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00001_196341_1517807318207
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the Committee has established, adopted or recognised standard specifications for`
  line `textiles either for internal consumption or for the purposes of export or has established, adopted or`
  line `recognised standard type of textile machinery and on the recommendation made to it in this behalf the`
  line `Central Government is of opinion that any textiles or textile machinery which do not conform to the`
  line `standards laid by the Committee in respect thereof, should not be exported or sold for internal`
  line `consumption the Central Government may, by order published in the Official Gazette, prohibit such`
  line `export or sale.`
  line
  line `(2) If any person contravenes any order issued under sub-section (1) prohibiting--`
  line
  line `(a) the export of any textiles or textile machinery, or`
  line
  line `(b) the sale of any textiles or textile machinery for internal consumption,`
  line
  line `he shall, on conviction, be punishable,--`
  line
  line `(i) for the first offence with imprisonment for a term which may extend to one year or with`
  line `fine or with both;`
  line
  line `(ii) for the second or a subsequent offence with imprisonment for a term which may extend to`
  line `one year and also with fine and in the absence of special and adequate reasons to be mentioned in`
  line `the judgment of the court, such imprisonment shall not be less than three months.`
  line
  line `(3) Any court trying the contravention of an order prohibiting the marketing of textiles or textile`
  line `machinery under sub-section (1) may, without prejudice to the provisions of clause (b) of sub-section (2),`
  line `direct that the textiles or textile machinery in respect of which the court is satisfied that such`
  line `contravention has been committed, shall be forfeited to the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (25939)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 25
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00001_196341_1517807318207&sectionId=25939&sectionno=18&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00001_196341_1517807318207
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the person committing any offence under this Act is a company,`
  line `every person who, at the time the offence was committed was in charge of, and was responsible to, the`
  line `company for the conduct of business of the company, as well as the company, shall be deemed to be`
  line `guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to such`
  line `punishment provided in this Act if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or`
  line `that he exercised all due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where an offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a company, and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the consent or`
  line `connivance of, or is attributable to any negligence on the part of, any director, manager, secretary or other`
  line `officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall also be deemed to be guilty`
  line `of that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section--`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means a body corporate and includes a firm or other association of`
  line `individuals; and`
  line
  line `(b) "director", in relation to a firm, means a partner in the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (25940)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 26
  title `Procedure for prosecution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00001_196341_1517807318207&sectionId=25940&sectionno=19&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00001_196341_1517807318207
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `No prosecution for any offence punishable under this Act shall be`
  line `instituted except by or with the consent of the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (25941)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 27
  title `Jurisdiction of courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00001_196341_1517807318207&sectionId=25941&sectionno=20&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00001_196341_1517807318207
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `No court inferior to that of a Presidency Magistrate or a Magistrate of`
  line `the first class, shall try any offence punishable under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (25942)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 28
  title `Protection of action taken under the Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00001_196341_1517807318207&sectionId=25942&sectionno=21&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00001_196341_1517807318207
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall`
  line `lie against the committee or any member, officer or employee of the Committee for anything which is in`
  line `good faith done or intended to be done in pursuance of this Act or of any rule or regulation`
  line `made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (25943)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 29
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00001_196341_1517807318207&sectionId=25943&sectionno=22&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00001_196341_1517807318207
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, subject to the condition of previous`
  line `publication, by notification in the Official Gazette, make rules for carrying out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power such rules`
  line `provide for--`
  line
  line `(a) the number of members and the composition of the Committee and the manner in which the`
  line `members shall be chosen;`
  line
  line `(b) the term of offence of and the manner of filling casual vacancies among the members of`
  line `the Committee;`
  line
  line `(c) the allowances, if any, payable to the members of the Committee;`
  line
  line `(d) the disqualification for membership of the Committee;`
  line
  line `^1[(da) the manner in which the duty of excise leviable under section 5A may be assessed, paid or`
  line `collected, and the manner in which any refund of such duty paid or collected in excess of the amount`
  line `due may be made;`
  line
  line `(db) the conditions of service of the person constituting the Tribunal under section 5B;`
  line
  line `(dc) the form and the manner in which an appeal to the Tribunal constituted under section 5B`
  line `may be preferred and verified the fees payable on such appeals and the procedure to be followed by`
  line `the Tribunal in disposing of such appeals;]`
  line
  line `(e) the scale of fees that may be levied ^2*** under section 12;`
  line
  line `(f) the form in which the Committee shall prepare its annual statement of accounts and`
  line balance-sheet;
  line
  line `(g) the method of appointment, the conditions of service and the scale of pay of the Secretary of`
  line `the Committee;`
  line
  line `(h) the collection of any information or statistics in respect of textile industry and trade and the`
  line `manufacture of textile machinery;`
  line
  line `(i) the mode of inspection by the Committee and the manner in which samples may be taken by it;`
  line
  line `^1[(j) any other matter which has to be, or may be, prescribed.]`
  line
  line `^3[(3) Every rule made by the Central Government under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after`
  line `it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session for a total period of thirty days which`
  line `may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the`
  line `session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in`
  line `making any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall,`
  line `thereafter, have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be, so however that`
  line `any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done`
  line `under that rule.]`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 51 of 1973, s. 10 (w.e.f. 1-1-1975).`
  line
  line `2. The words "for inspection and examination" omitted by s. 10, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-1-1975).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 10, ibid., for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 1-1-1975).`
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (25944)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 30
  title `Power to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00001_196341_1517807318207&sectionId=25944&sectionno=23&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00001_196341_1517807318207
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Committee may, with the previous sanction of the Central`
  line `Government, by notification in the Official Gazette, make regulations not inconsistent with this Act and`
  line `the rules made thereunder to provide for all matters for which provision is necessary or expedient for the`
  line `purpose of giving effect to the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such regulations may`
  line `provide for--`
  line
  line `(a) the meeting of the Committee, Standing Committees and ad hoc Committees, the quorum for`
  line `such meetings and the conduct of business thereat;`
  line
  line `(b) the allowances payable to the members of the Standing Committees or the ad hoc`
  line Committees;
  line
  line `(c) the methods of appointment, the conditions of service and the scales of pay of the officers`
  line `(other than the Secretary) and other employees of the Committee;`
  line
  line `(d) the duties and conduct of officers and other employees of the Committee; and`
  line
  line `(e) any other matter in respect of which the Committee is empowered or required to make`
  line `regulations under this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, amend, vary or rescind any`
  line `regulation which it has sanctioned; and thereupon the regulation shall have effect accordingly, but without`
  line `prejudice to the exercise of the powers of the Committee under sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (25945)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 31
  title `Repeal and Saving.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00001_196341_1517807318207&sectionId=25945&sectionno=24&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00001_196341_1517807318207
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) With effect from the date on which the Committee is established under`
  line `section 3, the Cotton Textiles Fund Ordinance, 1944 (34 of 1944), shall stand repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding the repeal of the said Ordinance,--`
  line
  line `(a) all moneys at the credit of the Cotton Textiles Fund established under the repealed Ordinance`
  line `immediately before the said date shall with effect from the said date stand transferred to and form part`
  line `of the Textiles Fund referred to in section 7;`
  line
  line `(b) any rules made or deemed to have been made or anything done or any action taken in exercise`
  line `of any of the powers conferred by or under the said Ordinance shall be deemed to have been made,`
  line `done or taken in exercise of the powers conferred by or under this Act, as if this Act were in force on`
  line `the day on which such rules were made, such thing was done or such action was taken.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
